The bounds suggested in Corollary 3.1 are for small \epsilon perturbations of the nominal model in terms of the variance of the marginal performance measure Hg and the FIM. Recall that Hg is related to the distribution of the QoI given the distribution of input parameters. Reminiscent of the variance-bias tradeoff of other information-based criteria for assessing model selection in statistics (for example, the Akaike information criterion and the Bayesian information criterion [8]), importantly (22) is a goal-oriented quantity that incorporates the output of the forward model Hg.
Corollary 3.1 follows from the general noninfinitesimal linearization (13) by noticing that the relative entropy has the expansion

